FBIS4-495 "drafr070_c_94034" FBIS-AFR-94-070 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA TEC Assures Public Servants of Job Security TEC Assures Public Servants of Job Security MB0904082594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 9 Apr 94 MB0904082594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Transitional Executive Council [TEC] has assured all public servants that their future is safe after the elections. In a statement the TEC asks public servants to give their full support to assure good administration and security during the elections. They are not to take part in disruptive activities such as strikes. The statement referred public servants to the provisions of the new constitution that provides for any person employed in any government department on 27 April to be retained in service after elections.
